Scripted modifiers work like scripted effects and triggers.

Can be invoked without parameters using "name = yes", or can take any number of parameters.

They are used in weights and have nothing to do with country modifiers.

== Example modifier ==
example_modifier = {
	modifier = {
		add = { value = 10 multiply = $SCALE$ }
		$CHARACTER_1$ = {
			has_trait = ambitious
		}
	}
	opinion_modifier = {
		target = $CHARACTER_2$
		who = $CHARACTER_1$
		multiplier = { value = 0.25 multiply = $SCALE$ }
	}
	compare_modifier = {
		target = $CHARACTER_1$
		value = stress
		multiplier = $SCALE$
	}
}

== Example invocation ==
random_list = {
	1 = {
		example_modifier = {
			CHARACTER_1 = root
			CHARACTER_2 = root
			SCALE = 0.1
		}
	}
}

Also, they can intake parameter values:
Exmaple Text: "Grateful Families in [SCOPE.GetRootScope.GetCountry.GetName]: $VALUE|+=$"

For example modifier:
approval_modifier_grateful_family = {
	modifier = { # Grateful Family Modifier
		trigger = {
			any_family = {
				is_grateful = yes
			}
		}
		add = {
			every_family = {
				limit = {
					is_grateful = yes
				}
				add = $VALUE$ # Value being subtracted for every Grateful Family
			}
		}
		desc = APPROVAL_MODIFIER_GRATEFUL_FAMILY
	}
}